\begin_layout Standard
A species tree in the ClonalOrigin framework can include recombinant edges,
 each of which exists only over a variable region of an alignment block.
 A recombinant edge departs at an older time of one of the species tree
 branches, and arrives at an earlier time of another branch.
 As a reference species tree starts from one side to another along the alignment
, and meets a recombinant edge, the arrival branch of the species tree is
 detached and regrafted to the departure point of the departure branch.
 The species tree sequentially change along the alignment.
 The number of recombinant edges along all of the alignment blocks could
 indicate overall recombination event intensity.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
